08757nam a22011775i 9783110476675DE-B159720210621102733.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210621t20192019gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831104766757 a10.1515/97831104766752doi  a(DE-B1597)465987  a(OCoLC)1110707863  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aN6490b.H36 2019 7aART0151102bisacsh04a700.41100aHandbook of Art and Global Migration :bTheories, Practices, and Challenges /ced. by Burcu Dogramaci, Birgit Mersmann. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2019] 4c©2019  a1 online resource (428 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENT -- tArt and Global Migration. Theories, Practices, and Challenges -- tMigratory Challenges for Art Production and Art History -- tToward a Migratory Turn -- tFrom Global Turbulences to Spaces of Conviviality -- tThe Migrant Image -- tImmigrants, Refugees and the Arts -- tAesthetics and Art Practices of Migration -- tClose Encounters -- tFuocoammare and the Aesthetic Rendition of the Relational Experience of Migration -- tPaths Walked Twice -- tWomen, Art, Migration and Diaspora -- tMigratory Networks. Objects and Actors on the Route -- tOn Nomadic Textile Forms – The Aesthetic of Nomadic Textiles -- tCosmopolitan Nodes and Vectors -- tPhotodocumentaries of Global Migration -- tClimates of Displacement -- tPlaces, Spaces, and Boundaries of Migration -- tFrom Baghdad to Paris and back -- tThe Place of Faith -- tThe Migratory Living Room -- tOf Inner Cities and Outer Space -- tHistories and Memories of Migration -- tMemory. Belonging. Engaging. -- tMigration, Dispossession, Post-Memorial Recuperations -- tMigration on Display -- tExhibiting Voids -- tBeyond Migration. Post-migratory Concepts and Strategies -- tWhen Migration Turns from the Spectacular to the Ordinary -- tMigration and Postmigration as New Frameworks for Art Theory -- tPostmigrant Practices of Living as Resistance -- tThe Postmigrant Condition in Fashion, Culture and Fashion Theory -- tIMAGE CREDITS -- tBIOGRAPHIES OF THE AUTHORS -- tINDEX0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aHow can we think of art history as a discipline that moves process-based, performative, and cultural migratory movement to the center of its theoretical and methodical analyses? With contributions from internationally renowned experts, this manual, for the first time, provides answers as to what consequences the interaction of migration and globalization has on research in the field of the science of art, on curatory practice, and on artistic production and theory. The objective of this multi-vocal anthology is to open up an interdisciplinary discourse surrounding the increased focus on the phenomenon of migration in art history.  aWie lässt sich eine Kunstgeschichte denken, die prozessuale, performative und transkulturelle Wanderungsbewegungen ins Zentrum ihrer theoretischen und methodischen Analysen rückt? Mit Beiträgen international ausgewiesener Experten gibt das Handbuch erstmals Antworten darauf, welche Konsequenzen das Zusammenwirken von Migration und Globalisierung für die kunstwissenschaftliche Forschung, die kuratorische Praxis sowie die künstlerische Produktion und Theorie hat. Ziel der vielstimmigen Anthologie ist es, einen interdisziplinären Diskurs zum „migratory turn" in der Kunstgeschichte zu eröffnen.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aArts and globalization. 0aArts and history. 0aArts and society. 0aGlobalization. 7aART / History / Contemporary (1945-).2bisacsh1 aBal, Mieke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBublatzky, Cathrine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDasgupta, Su